### 1.12 Backend — Build `server.js` (The Entire Backend in 1 File)

#### Step 1: Basic Setup
- [ ] Add `require('express')`, `require('mongoose')`, `require('cors')`, `require('dotenv')`
- [ ] Call `dotenv.config()`
- [ ] Create Express app: `const app = express()`
- [ ] Set PORT: `const PORT = process.env.PORT || 5050`
- [ ] Add `app.use(cors())`
- [ ] Add `app.use(express.json())`

#### Step 2: Optional MongoDB Connection
- [ ] Add `let dbConnected = false`
- [ ] Add `if (process.env.MONGO_URI)` block → `mongoose.connect()` 
- [ ] Add `.then()` → set `dbConnected = true`, log success
- [ ] Add `.catch()` → log warning, continue with in-memory
- [ ] Add `else` block → log "using in-memory store"

#### Step 3: In-Memory Database — Users
- [ ] Create `const db = {}` object
- [ ] Add `db.users` array with 3 demo users:
  - User 1: id `u1`, name `Aditya`, email, role `deaf`, points `3845`, level `7`, streak `32`
  - User 2: id `u2`, name `Priya`, email, role `blind`, points `4210`, level `8`, streak `45`
  - User 3: id `u3`, name `Rahul`, email, role `deaf`, points `2950`, level `6`, streak `18`

#### Step 4: In-Memory Database — Lessons
- [ ] Add `db.lessons` array with 5 lessons:
  - Lesson 1: Sign Language Basics (beginner, 15min, 50pts)
  - Lesson 2: Advanced Signing Practice (advanced, 45min, 120pts)
  - Lesson 3: Audio Storytelling 101 (beginner, 20min, 60pts)
  - Lesson 4: STEM Vocabulary in Sign Language (intermediate, 60min, 150pts)
  - Lesson 5: Braille Reading Fundamentals (beginner, 25min, 80pts)

#### Step 5: In-Memory Database — Progress
- [ ] Add `db.progress` object:
  - `u1`: completedLessons `["l1"]`, currentLesson `"l2"`, weeklyMinutes `275`
  - `u2`: completedLessons `["l3", "l5"]`, currentLesson `"l4"`, weeklyMinutes `310`
  - `u3`: completedLessons `["l1"]`, currentLesson `"l2"`, weeklyMinutes `120`

#### Step 6: In-Memory Database — Posts
- [ ] Add `db.posts` array with 3 forum posts:
  - Post 1: by u1, "Tips for practicing signing daily"
  - Post 2: by u2, "Best audio textbooks for physics?"
  - Post 3: by u3, "Anyone interested in a weekly signing meetup?"

#### Step 7: In-Memory Database — Badges
- [ ] Add `db.badges` array with 3 badges:
  - Badge 1: "Signing Scholar" — award icon
  - Badge 2: "Perfect Streak" — star icon
  - Badge 3: "Community Guide" — users icon

#### Step 8: Auto-Increment Counters
- [ ] Add `let nextPostId = db.posts.length + 1`
- [ ] Add `let nextUserId = db.users.length + 1`

#### Step 9: Routes — Root + API Index
- [ ] `GET /` → return JSON: name, version, docs link, database status
- [ ] `GET /api` → return JSON: object listing all available endpoints

#### Step 10: Routes — Health
- [ ] `GET /api/health` → return `{ status: "ok", uptime, database }`

#### Step 11: Routes — Auth (Mock)
- [ ] `POST /api/auth/login` → extract `email` from body → find user by email or fallback to first user → return `{ token, user }`
- [ ] `POST /api/auth/register` → extract `name, email, role` → validate required → check duplicate email → create new user → add to `db.users` → init progress → return `{ token, user }`

#### Step 12: Routes — Users
- [ ] `GET /api/users` → return `db.users`
- [ ] `GET /api/users/:id` → find by id → 404 if not found → return user

#### Step 13: Routes — Lessons
- [ ] `GET /api/lessons` → filter by `category` and `level` query params → return filtered list
- [ ] `GET /api/lessons/:id` → find by id → 404 if not found → return lesson

#### Step 14: Routes — Progress
- [ ] `GET /api/progress/:userId` → lookup in `db.progress` → 404 if not found → return
- [ ] `POST /api/progress/:userId/complete` → extract `lessonId` → validate user + lesson exist → add lesson to completedLessons (if not already) → add points to user → add minutes → return `{ user, progress }`

#### Step 15: Routes — Community
- [ ] `GET /api/community/posts` → sort by `createdAt` descending → return
- [ ] `POST /api/community/posts` → extract `userId, title, body` → validate all required → find author → create post object → add to `db.posts` → return 201

#### Step 16: Routes — Leaderboard + Badges
- [ ] `GET /api/leaderboard` → sort users by `points` descending → take top 10 → return
- [ ] `GET /api/badges` → return `db.badges`

#### Step 17: Routes — 404 Catch-All
- [ ] `app.use()` → return 404 JSON with method + path

#### Step 18: Start Server
- [ ] `app.listen(PORT, () => console.log(...))`

